Helping students at Bosco Jomo who don’t usually get a chance to learn has taught me the value of giving time to others. I go once a week for an hour and a half, and during that time, they share how hard it is to live away from their parents. Their stories inspire me to work harder in my studies and learn ICT so I can create learning opportunities for students without resources. I plan to do this by developing simple digital tools, online lessons, and small programs to make studying easier and interactive. To make learning fun, I create games and read long essays with them. After tutoring, we play basketball, and I enjoy organizing zone games where everyone tries different positions, learning patience and teamwork. My spiritual school and community support help me approach all these activities with care and love
